reviewText:
My opinion on this game is negative. Here's why:
Task(s?) and game mechanism are horribly explained, mostly because of some very bad English but also because everything is explained as if it is obvious, but believe me it is not;
the human-character's face aesthetics are the worst. In years of gaming, I've never had hated a videogame character just because of how they look. Now I have.
terrible, terrible main map; as boring as it is big (and we have some piece of pointlessy huge map here);
terrible, terrible graphics: it made me check the year when the first Half-Life was released;
enemies stop considering you as soon as you stop shooting at them. Also you need to empty like 4 or 5 plasma magazines before killing one and that feels really overdone. Also they keep respawning one friggin' minute after you kill 'em;
if you die you have to start from the beginning of that piece of tedium map;
robot-character sometimes stop running for no apparent reason;
generally nothing in this game is entertaining;
generally everything in this game is boring and grinding.Achievements are initially easy to get but even this turns into a grind-fest very rapidly (kill 100, 200, 1000 enemies? Really? I killed 25 of them and I can't stop yawning already).
I bought this game on sale for 0,39€, played 37 minutes then idled it for the rest of the cards, that I sold for 0,11€. Absolutely NOT recommended to get this game at its full price.
